   =20
      Golf
   =20
 =20

One thing that I  think   about  a   lot is how, back when Goldman Sachs Ch=
ief Executive Officer David Solomon (who is also a DJ) was fairly new on th=
e job and was doing a lot of press about also being a DJ, he  told Jen Wiec=
zner at Fortune that other bankers almost thwarted his dream (of being CEO =
of Goldman Sachs and also a DJ):
Some advisers told him to hang it up. =E2=80=9CI thought for a minute, Well=
, can I do this, can I not do this?=E2=80=9D recalls Solomon, who donates t=
he proceeds from his gigs and Spotify plays to drug-addiction-related phila=
nthropies. ... Those doubts soon dispersed, especially after his boss at th=
e time, then-CEO Lloyd Blankfein, and others endorsed it. =E2=80=9CYou know=
 what, it=E2=80=99s who I am, and nobody would tell me not to play golf,=E2=
=80=9D Solomon says now.=C2=A0
One reason I think about this a lot is that, as  Insider reported last Sept=
ember,=C2=A0=E2=80=9CSolomon has recently been working on his golf game and=
 has sought out memberships at some of the country=E2=80=99s most prestigio=
us golf clubs and courses.=E2=80=9D He=E2=80=99s right; nobody told him not=
 to play golf. The lesson here might be that if you are a high-level invest=
ment banker you are=C2=A0allowed=C2=A0to be a DJ, but you are=C2=A0required=
=C2=A0to be a golfer.
Greg Lemkau, Goldman=E2=80=99s former co-head of investment banking, knows.=
 Here is eFinancialCareers:

Lemkau spoke on the Capital Allocators podcast with Ted Seides earlier this=
 week, and explained the career benefits of his favorite game.
=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s a great way to spend four hours outside,=E2=80=9D Lem=
kau said of golf, although he admitted that he still isn=E2=80=99t great at=
 it. He added that it =E2=80=9Camazes=E2=80=9D him how few people understan=
d golf's value in business.
=E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t care how brilliant I might have been in any meetin=
g, never once did a client say =E2=80=9CGod, remember that time we flipped =
through that blue book, and you took me through that DCF? Wasn=E2=80=99t th=
at magical?=E2=80=9D=E2=80=9D He joked. =E2=80=9CBut the amount of times I=
=E2=80=99ve heard =E2=80=9Cdo you remember that time we spent four hours on=
 this golf course or that golf course?=E2=80=9D

One important lesson there is that being a high-level investment banker is =
primarily a social activity; the job is to befriend important people, not t=
o be good at discounted cash flow analyses. (This is relevant to, for insta=
nce, the big banks=E2=80=99   =E2=80=9Cprinceling=E2=80=9D hiring scandals =
from a few years ago: A shortcut to befriending important people is just be=
ing their children.) Another lesson is that, when junior investment bankers=
 work all night formatting pitchbooks, that work is almost certainly wasted=
, and the deals are being won on the golf course. Friends do not exchange p=
itchbooks with each other.
Another lesson is subtly conveyed by =E2=80=9Cthis golf course or that golf=
 course=E2=80=9D: The course matters.=C2=A0The clients are not like =E2=80=
=9Cit was so nice spending four hours getting exercise in the open air with=
 you=E2=80=9D; they are like =E2=80=9Cit was so nice getting access to a pr=
estigious golf club with you.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0To be a successful banker you d=
on=E2=80=99t absolutely=C2=A0need=C2=A0to develop a true friendship with th=
e clients; giving them prestigious and valuable gifts =E2=80=94=C2=A0like a=
 tee time at Pine Valley =E2=80=94=C2=A0is a reasonable substitute. Around =
here   I often=C2=A0quote the most important thing I learned at Goldman,=C2=
=A0John Whitehead=E2=80=99s  commandment to relationship bankers that =E2=
=80=9CImportant people like to deal with important people. Are you one?=E2=
=80=9D Important people like to play golf with important people at importan=
t golf clubs.
  [5]

Also though how many clients do you think do deals with Goldman and reminis=
ce with David Solomon =E2=80=9Cdo you remember that time I listened to your=
   DJ set opening for the Chainsmokers=C2=A0in Water Mill?=E2=80=9D It=E2=
=80=99s a hobby, and I suppose in its way it might impress clients, but it =
is distinctly less=C2=A0social=C2=A0than golf. You need golf too.

