      How is Razzlekhan doing?
   =20
 =20

 Okay!

The former tech entrepreneur, =E2=80=9CRazzlekhan=E2=80=9D rapper and accus=
ed cryptocurrency thief Heather Morgan has a new job.
Morgan, who dubbed herself on social media and in music videos as =E2=80=9C=
The Crocodile of Wall Street,=E2=80=9D was hired by an unspecified technolo=
gy company even though she=E2=80=99s under 24-hour house arrest, according =
to a court filing. She and her husband are accused of trying to launder $4.=
5 billion of Bitcoin stolen from the Bitfinex currency exchange.
She asked a judge to modify the terms of her home confinement so she can wo=
rk three days a week from the employer=E2=80=99s New York office. The gover=
nment doesn=E2=80=99t object to the proposed modification, her lawyer, Euge=
ne Gorokhov, said in the filing Tuesday in Washington.
Morgan, who has denied wrongdoing, was offered a job =E2=80=9Cin the role o=
f growth marketing and business development specialist,=E2=80=9D Gorokhov s=
aid in the filing. He told the court that she=E2=80=99s seeking to keep the=
 name of the employer secret to protect her safety, though the government i=
s aware of the identity.

I have to say that she is probably the only business rapper whose stage nam=
e I know? And, no offense, not because she is so great at rapping? But beca=
use   getting arrested for a multibillion-dollar Bitcoin heist brings a lot=
 of publicity to your business rapping career? Like, that=E2=80=99s a growt=
h marketing success right there, sure.

